     Well, here it is.  The easiest method for CHEATING at Bards Tale.  I got
tired of all the mis- and partial information floating around about the
character data format for the Bards Tale Characters.  Use this program at
your own risk.

     Now to more productive notes.

   When you start the program, it will prompt you to put your character disk
in a drive (unless its already there), and will put up a requester with your
characters names.  Click the one you want, or you can type the name into the
string gadget manually.  When your character is loaded, the data for your
character will be displayed on the screen.

****************
NOTE: If you enter a name that doesn't exist on the disk, the program will
	complain to you, but will go ahead and display the character anyway.
	The stats for this new character will be zeros if you have just
	started the editor, or the stats of the last edited character.
      If you enter a null name, the editor will tell you it could not find
      "NIEMAND" on the disk.  DON'T PANIC!  Niemand is the German word
       for "nobody."  Niemand will then be shown with stats as in the note
       above.
****************

     After your character is loaded, you will be able to access several
menus at the top of the screen.

  The menus are:

Project
